label: Starting dilution fold
description: the fold change from the starting concentration of a solution being diluted

label: Starting concentration (ug/mL)
description: the initial amount of antibody dissolved in the solution being diluted, reported in ug/mL

label: 4-PL curve parameter A
description: the minimum value that can be obtained

label: 4-PL curve parameter D
description: the maximum value that can be obtained

label: 4-PL curve R2
description: a statistical measure of fit that indicates how much variation of a dependent variable is explained by the independent variable(s)

label: ULOD (ng/mL)
description: the upper limit of detection in ng/ml

label: LLOD (ng/mL)
description: the lower limit of detection in ng/ml

label: geometric mean concentration (ELU/mL)
description: The average antibody concentration for a group of subjects calculated by multiplying all values and taking the nth root of this number, where n is the number of subjects with available data.(GMC)
